2. I

UB %<>%
  data.frame() %>%                                                      # Data Frame   
  mutate(Personal.Loan = ifelse(Personal.Loan == 1, "yes", "no")) %>%   # Target   
  select(-1)                                                            # ID  

# Convert to Factor
fac.col <- c("Family", "Education", "Securities.Account", 
             "CD.Account", "Online", "CreditCard",
             # Target
             "Personal.Loan")

UB <- UB %>% 
  mutate_at(fac.col, as.factor)                                         #

4. 

# Partition (Training Dataset : Test Dataset = 7:3)
y      <- UB$Personal.Loan                            # Target
 
set.seed(200)
ind    <- createDataPartition(y, p = 0.7, list = T)   # Index  7:3 
UB.trd <- UB[ind$Resample1,]                          # Training Dataset
UB.ted <- UB[-ind$Resample1,]                         # Test Dataset

5. II

# 1. Standardization
preProcValues <- preProcess(UB.trd, 
                            method = c("center", "scale"))  # Training Dataset     

UB.trd <- predict(preProcValues, UB.trd)                    #  for Training Dataset
UB.ted <- predict(preProcValues, UB.ted)                    #  for Test Dataset

6.

Package "glmnet" glmnet() LASSO Regression . glmnet() Target 2 , Factor (Level) . , a b 2 Target Factor a b, a, b . glmnet() .

glmnet(x, y, family, alpha, lambda, ...)
  • x :
  • y : Target
  • family : Target
    • "gaussian" : Target
    • "binomial" : 2 Target
    • "multinomial" : 3 Target
    • "poisson" : Count Data Target
  • alpha : Elasticnet Mixing Parameter
    • 0 : Ridge Regression
    • 1 : Lasso Regression
    • 0 < alpha < 1 : Elastic Net Regression
  • lambda : Regularization Parameter
    • .
    • 100 lambda .

set.seed(200)                                          # Seed  ->    
cv.lasso.fit <- cv.glmnet(x = train.x,                 #

                          nfolds = 5,                  # 5-Fold Cross Validation
                          type.measure = "auc")        # AUC

1) Package pROC

pacman::p_load("pROC")

lasso.roc  <- roc(ac, pp, plot = T, col = "gray")      # roc( class,  )
auc        <- round(auc(lasso.roc), 3)
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")

Caution! Package "pROC" ROC .

#  plot.roc() 
plot.roc(lasso.roc,   
         col="gray",                                   # Line Color
         print.auc = TRUE,                             # AUC  
         print.auc.col = "red",                        # AUC  
         print.thres = TRUE,                           # Cutoff Value  
         print.thres.pch = 19,                         # Cutoff Value   
         print.thres.col = "red",                      # Cutoff Value   
         auc.polygon = TRUE,                           #     
         auc.polygon.col = "gray90")                   #    

#  ggroc() 
ggroc(lasso.roc) +
annotate(geom = "text", x = 0.9, y = 1.0,
label = paste("AUC = ", auc),
size = 5,
color="red") +
theme_bw()

3) Package ROCR

pacman::p_load("ROCR")

lasso.pred <- prediction(pp, ac)                       # prediction( ,  class) 

lasso.perf <- performance(lasso.pred, "tpr", "fpr")    # performance(, "", "1-")                      
plot(lasso.perf, col = "gray")                         # ROC Curve

perf.auc   <- performance(lasso.pred, "auc")           # AUC
auc        <- attributes(perf.auc)$y.values
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")
